= Custom Houdini Procedural =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Assigns a Houdini Procedural to a specified USD primitive for rendering."""

== Overview ==

Custom Houdini Procedural configures a USD primitive to be rendered using a Houdini Procedural. A Houdini Procedural is a plugin that generates geometry at render time from a SOP graph.

WARNING:
    The Karma/Mantra render command must include the argument `--allowed-procedurals all` unless the procedural outputs only curves or points.

@parameters

Graph File:
    #id: graph_file
    SOP-level graph file provided as input to the procedural.

Procedural Name:
    #id: proc_name
    Name of the registered Houdini Procedural.

Procedural Primitive:
    #id: proc_prim
    The USD primitive to configure as a Houdini Procedural.

Inputs:
    #id: inputs
    USD primitives to use as inputs to the SOP graph.

Overrides:
    #id: overrides
    Overrides for SOP graph parameters and USD primitive properties.
